{"author":{"id":"3d0aa6b92642a75351eecf58e034d3e1459d91c213ae81865834e0d76d80d94b"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1456781543,"nonce":"k35AsrWYC6URtK7oLenLpLa5Rc0=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE5MDQwNTc3MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/603#issuecomment-190405771"},"message":"The issue here is that the above validation transforms the value into a string and back. This is inconsistent and leads to undesired consequences. In https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy/pull/1764 the validation call has been modified to use the regular check_param caller (see: https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy/pull/1764/files#diff-1bef786a2b2ea704c1748e41cd25dd33R1251). I also suggest to remove the validation in the execute caller since a validation error leads to an ungraceful fail as we can see above. It also breaks the job resubmission and workflow pausing feature. I think that a new validation point at an earlier stage could be reasonable, if this turns out to be true I will introduce it for 16.04.","files":null}]}